Get your team on the same page

The Team Canvas is Business Model Canvas for teamwork. It is a free tool for leaders, facilitators and consultants to organize team alignment meetings and bring members on the same page, resolve conflicts and build productive culture, fast.

Available in: English, Español, Русский. We don't spam.

Downloaded and used by team leaders and facilitators at

Why Use Team Canvas

As a leader or facilitator, you experience moments when you need to bring team members together, clarify their goals, figure out their motivations and help them to be more aligned and productive.

Use Team Canvas to start a structured conversation with the team and bring everyone on the same page. Groups that go through Team Canvas sessions report higher clarity and alignment, with less friction and conflict.

In the long run, use Team Canvas to start shaping the team culture at your company or collective.

Learn how Team Canvas works.

Who Is It For

Team Leads

If you lead teams, you probably know how hard it may be to make everyone happy and productive in the group. Team Canvas provides you with a structured set of topics to achieve a much-needed state of alignment.

Facilitators

If you work with groups, you might have noticed how important it is to create a shared context and let everyone in the group be proactive and driven. Team Canvas is a tool from facilitators for facilitators: we just want our work to be more fun.

Educators

If your success as an educator is determined by how well your students get along while absorbing knowledge and and working on projects together, use Team Canvas to help students create stronger collectives.

Run The Team Canvas Session

Option A: Run a team meeting

Learn about Team Canvas and then use our elaborate How To Guide to facilitate internal meeting with your team.

Option B: Online Team Canvas

For remote teams, we recommend using one of collaborative brainstorming tools to run Team Canvas session with the whole team along with a Skype/Google hangouts call.

Option C: Get online training

Sign up for an online course to learn how to use Team Canvas, facilitate team meetings and combine it with other tools.
